    {
      "type": "note",
      "spec_version": "2.1",
      "id": "note--fezbox-assessment-001",
      "created": "2026-04-03T02:00:00.000Z",
      "modified": "2026-04-03T02:00:00.000Z",
      "content": "Assessment: FEZBOX operator is likely a Chinese security researcher or student building a supply chain attack demonstration tool. The 'Educational Use Only' labeling, PyCharm development environment, and self-testing pattern suggest academic or portfolio motivation rather than professional cybercrime. However, the npm package was real and could have affected any developer who installed it during the 32-day window. The C2 remains live 7+ months after npm seized the package, indicating the operator has not abandoned the infrastructure.",
